        "contact": {
          "url": "https://sunrise-sunset.org/api"
        },
        "description": "Provides sunset and sunrise times for a given latitude and longitude using a simple REST API. Attribution is required when using this API.",
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://api.sunrise-sunset.org"
          }
        ],
        "termsOfService": "https://sunrise-sunset.org/terms-of-use",
        "title": "Sunset Times API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Sunrise, sunset, twilight and solar noon times for any latitude/longitude worldwide",
        "homepage": "https://sunrise-sunset.org",
        "docs_url": "https://sunrise-sunset.org/api",
        "license_short": "Free to use with reasonable request volume; attribution with a link back to sunrise-sunset.org is required.",
        "license_md": "- Free service for sunrise/sunset data with no authentication required.\n- Attribution is required: link back to [sunrise-sunset.org](https://sunrise-sunset.org).\n- Usage must not exceed reasonable request volume.\n- No published rate limit, but excessive traffic may be throttled.",
        "about_md": "[Sunrise Sunset](https://sunrise-sunset.org) is a small REST API that returns sunrise, sunset and twilight times for any point on Earth. The service is hosted at `https://api.sunrise-sunset.org` and is free to use without an API key.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- `sunrise`, `sunset` and `solar_noon` times\n- `day_length` in seconds (or formatted)\n- Civil, nautical and astronomical twilight begin/end times\n- Optional timezone-aware output via the `tzid` parameter (e.g. `UTC`, `Africa/Lagos`)\n- JSONP support via the `callback` parameter\n\nThe single endpoint is `GET /json` with required `lat` and `lng` query parameters and optional `date` (YYYY-MM-DD, defaults to today), `formatted` (0 or 1), `tzid` and `callback`. Responses include a `status` field with values such as `OK`, `INVALID_REQUEST`, `INVALID_DATE`, `INVALID_TZID` or `UNKNOWN_ERROR`. CORS is enabled and attribution back to sunrise-sunset.org is expected.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "sunrise_and_sunset": "Sunrise, sunset, solar noon, day length and the three twilight phases (civil, nautical, astronomical) for a given latitude/longitude and optional date — served from `GET /json?lat={lat}&lng={lng}`."
        },
